OL,3,CChemical castration and early release
OL,4,Cof some domestic abusers to be
OL,5,Cintroduced
OL,7,FChemical suppression, or castration,
OL,8,Faims to reduce sexual offenders'
OL,9,Fcompulsive and invasive thoughts about
OL,10,Fsex.
OL,12,FOffenders receive chemical suppression
OL,13,Fvia two drugs. Selective serotonin
OL,14,Freuptake inhibitors (SSRIs) limit
OL,15,Finvasive sexual thoughts, while anti-
OL,16,Fandrogens work to reduce the
OL,17,Fproduction of testosterone and limit
OL,18,Flibido.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G17/20
